      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KEAYANG MEMORY (3) resumes from a spell of four-and-a-half months after closing off last campaign in good form, the last run being a solid third over 2040m at Parkes. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Sure to be right there at the finish. LOCHINVAR HAWK (1) finished fourth last start, beaten 9 metres at Gawler over 1609m. Capable of playing a major role so has to be respected. RUN AMUCK (2) last appeared when runner-up over 1790m at Mildura ten weeks ago. Keep an eye out for positive market movement. MURRA LANE (11) was out of the money two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he broke and finished a distant sixth over 1800m at this track. No favours expected from this draw. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back.",
